  "worthless_belief": [],
  "intermediate_belief": "If I don't succeed academically or financially, others will see me as a failure and I will let them down. I must avoid disappointing my mother or I will lose her approval. Depending on others for help means I am not capable or independent.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I can't handle things on my own and keep failing, there's no point in trying because nothing will change. My failures mean I will never be good enough, no matter what I do.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client tends to avoid discussing academic and financial issues to escape feelings of shame and anxiety. They withdraw from challenging situations and delay decisions about returning to college or seeking employment due to fear of failure. They also seek reassurance and financial support from their parents, which temporarily relieves anxiety but reinforces dependency.",
