  "behavior": "I avoid eye contact and keep the conversation brief. I don't bring up my plans or feelings. I accept the help but feel uncomfortable and withdrawn.",
  "rationale": "\"The academic underperformance, despite intelligence, may lead to feelings of frustration, inadequacy, and self-doubt.\" \"The high expectations from the mother might evoke feelings of pressure, anxiety, and fear of disappointing her.\" \"Financial difficulties and the need to seek help from parents could lead to feelings of embarrassment, shame, and dependency.\" \"The patient may engage in negative self-talk, characterized by thoughts of inadequacy and self-criticism due to their academic struggles.\" \"They may procrastinate on making decisions about returning to college or seeking employment due to fear of failure.\" \"The patient might also seek reassurance from their parents, which could perpetuate feelings of dependency and hinder their sense of independence.\""
